Times magazine in 2002, I found five of these

01:08:25.750 --> 01:08:30.040
trials that had been done and not been published
yet. And again, if we say, "Let's pretend

01:08:30.040 --> 01:08:34.750
this is a science," we have a hypothesis,
we have two of them. One of them is that saturated

01:08:34.750 --> 01:08:39.589
fat causes heart disease and one of them is
that if you eat more you'll get fat. So now,

01:08:39.589 --> 01:08:44.100
I'm gonna put you on a diet that says you
can eat as much as you want and as much saturated

01:08:44.100 --> 01:08:47.480
fat as you want and I recommend you do it.

01:08:47.480 --> 01:08:53.670
Our hypothesis predicts that you will gain
weight and get heart disease. And instead,

01:08:53.670 --> 01:08:59.170
what happened in these trials is these people
lose weight and their heart disease risk factors

01:08:59.170 --> 01:09:04.380
improve. Across the board, everything improves.
So the question then becomes, maybe our hypothesis

01:09:04.380 --> 01:09:05.380
is wrong.

