01:18:19.830 --> 01:18:24.330
Association diet. And they referred to it
as a low carb versus a low fat diet. This

01:18:24.330 --> 01:18:26.120
is a classic way to do it.

01:18:26.120 --> 01:18:30.960
But the low fat diet is calorie restricted.
So when you're told to go on the low fat diet,

01:18:30.960 --> 01:18:37.070
you're told to eat 14, 15 hundred calories
a day, basically semi-starve yourself. And

01:18:37.070 --> 01:18:42.520
when you go on the low carb diet, you're told
to eat as much as you want. Just don't eat

01:18:42.520 --> 01:18:44.110
carbohydrates.

01:18:44.110 --> 01:18:48.270
And one of the lessons I learned writing about
physics is it's absolutely crucial to define

01:18:48.270 --> 01:18:51.670
your terms carefully, so people know what
they've done and what you've done and can

01:18:51.670 --> 01:18:55.500
replicate it. And so, you're not in effect
trying to fool people.

01:18:55.500 --> 01:19:00.140
And if I was writing that study, it would
say "low fat, low calorie versus low carb,

01:19:00.140 --> 01:19:04.220
ad libitum. 'Ad libitum' means eat as much
as you want. And I would always use those

01:19:04.220 --> 01:19:08.750
terms because you never want them to forget
that one group is low calorie and one group

01:19:08.750 --> 01:19:12.660
is ad libitum. 'Cause that also suggests,
and in this case they got essentially the

01:19:12.660 --> 01:19:16.940
same weight loss. The Atkins group did better
on heart disease risk factors, but the weight

01:19:16.940 --> 01:19:18.810
loss was virtually the same.

01:19:18.810 --> 01:19:23.630
And you want people to remember that one group
is being semi-starved and one group isn't

01:19:23.630 --> 01:19:27.950
'cause that evidence that it’s not about
the calories. And they just didn't do it.

01:19:27.950 --> 01:19:33.280
They mentioned it in their methodology that
