01:24:21.890 --> 01:24:26.740
1970s, early 1980s, there was some research
done at the University of Vermont by a fellow

01:24:26.740 --> 01:24:31.000
named Steve Finney, who's now an emeritus
professor of nutrition at UC Davis.

01:24:31.000 --> 01:24:36.790
And he put professional bike racers on ketogenic
diets. And it takes about three weeks to what's

01:24:36.790 --> 01:24:43.740
called "ketoadopt," where you adopt completely
to the complete lack of carbs in the diet,

01:24:43.740 --> 01:24:47.770
in effect. And the bottom line was they did
fine. They lost a little bit of their sprinting

01:24:47.770 --> 01:24:52.920
ability, but they lost a lot of – they lost
