01:26:00.762 --> 01:26:02.900
&gt;&gt;Gary Taubes: I mean this is again, these
numbers, by the way, are very iffy.

01:26:02.900 --> 01:26:09.050
But certainly the question was, if you look
at the food consumption numbers, in the 1970s

01:26:09.050 --> 01:26:14.060
we were eating around 2200 calories. Then
it went up by 500 calories. So doesn't that

01:26:14.060 --> 01:26:17.880
prove that it’s about the calories? That's,
in effect, the, and the point is first of

01:26:17.880 --> 01:26:19.000
all, this is an observation.

01:26:19.000 --> 01:26:23.820
Remember I said, if somebody gets heavier,
they gotta eat more, or exercise less because

01:26:23.820 --> 01:26:29.440
they're gonna be in positive energy balance.
So even if, and it's pretty much assumed that

01:26:29.440 --> 01:26:33.440
food availability went up, our food portion
sizes got bigger, etc., etc.

01:26:33.440 --> 01:26:37.670
But did people get fatter because they consumed
more? Did they get hungrier because they were

01:26:37.670 --> 01:26:43.500
getting fatter? And those numbers don't, associations
like that tell you nothing about causality.

01:26:43.500 --> 01:26:49.230
They only tell you that two things happened
simultaneously.

01:26:49.230 --> 01:26:54.200
The price of tea in China probably also went
up since 1970, but we're not gonna blame obesity

01:26:54.200 --> 01:26:58.440
on that. Why would we blame it on the availability
of calories in the food supply? When you look

01:26:58.440 --> 01:27:04.630
at what those calories were, they were almost
exclusively carbohydrates and most of it was

01:27:04.630 --> 01:27:08.420
high fructose corn syrup.

01:27:08.420 --> 01:27:11.940
If you actually look at the number in fat,
it's something like three percent of the increase

01:27:11.940 --> 01:27:16.150
is from fat. Or actually fat -- the USDA has
screwed up the numbers and that's another

01:27:16.150 --> 01:27:20.700
story. But fat consumption, basically, went
down a little bit. Protein consumption went

01:27:20.700 --> 01:27:25.080
up a little bit and carbohydrate consumption
went up a lot. And it reflected the public

01:27:25.080 --> 01:27:32.370
health advice. The shift to pasta, breads,
potatoes and then this increase in sugar consumption

01:27:32.370 --> 01:27:36.930
that I believe was driven high fructose corn
syrup, by the fact that we first didn't know

01:27:36.930 --> 01:27:41.810
that high fructose corn syrup was sugar. And
second, believed it wasn't a problem because

01:27:41.810 --> 01:27:44.050
the problem was all about fat. Thank you.

